<paragraph blockId="73.[151,1437,1906,2041]" lastBlockId="75.[151,1437,153,1547]" lastPageId="75" lastPageNumber="76" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">
<emphasis box="[151,244,1906,1932]" italics="true" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">Female:</emphasis>
Body length 
<quantity box="[402,507,1906,1933]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.66" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" unit="mm" value="16.6">16.6 mm</quantity>
. Antenna with 22 antennomeres, antenna length 2.2 × head width; scape 1.6 × as long as than pedicel; scape length 3 × its width; pedicel length 2.5 × its width; 1 
<superScript attach="left" box="[1051,1062,1941,1955]" fontSize="6" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">st</superScript>
flagellomere 1.3 × as long as the 2 
<superScript attach="left" box="[165,181,1977,1991]" fontSize="6" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">nd</superScript>
flagellomere; antennae gradually tapering distally. In frontal view, lower interocular space 1.4 × eye length; face slightly rough, without reticulations (
<figureCitation box="[568,685,2014,2041]" captionStart="FIGURE 28" captionStartId="74.[151,250,1602,1627]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,166,1583]" captionTargetId="figure@74.[151,1436,166,1583]" captionTargetPageId="74" captionText="FIGURE 28. Derecyrta; a-g. Derecyrta risaraldensis sp. nov. ♀ (ICN-MHN ICN_095923); a. Habitus, lateral view, b. Habitus, dorsal view; c. Calcar; d. Head, frontal view; e. Head, lateral view; f. Fore wing; g. pretarsal claws; h. Distal metatarsus; i. D. beechei ♀ (SDEI, photograph by Taeger 2013) habitus, lateral view, j. D. circularis habitus ♀ (NMNH), lateral view. Abbrevia- tion of main veins in blue, cross veins in green, wing cells in red.A, Anal veins; a-a, anal crossvein; AP, proximal anal cell; AD, distal anal cell; C, costa; Cu, cubitus; M, media; r-m, radial-median crossvein; m-cu, mediocubital crossvein; R, radius; r-rs, radial crossvein; Rs, radial sector; Sc, Subcosta." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3335396/files/figure.png" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">Fig. 28d,c</figureCitation>
); vertex and temple smooth and polished (
<figureCitation box="[1160,1278,2014,2041]" captionStart="FIGURE 28" captionStartId="74.[151,250,1602,1627]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,166,1583]" captionTargetId="figure@74.[151,1436,166,1583]" captionTargetPageId="74" captionText="FIGURE 28. Derecyrta; a-g. Derecyrta risaraldensis sp. nov. ♀ (ICN-MHN ICN_095923); a. Habitus, lateral view, b. Habitus, dorsal view; c. Calcar; d. Head, frontal view; e. Head, lateral view; f. Fore wing; g. pretarsal claws; h. Distal metatarsus; i. D. beechei ♀ (SDEI, photograph by Taeger 2013) habitus, lateral view, j. D. circularis habitus ♀ (NMNH), lateral view. Abbrevia- tion of main veins in blue, cross veins in green, wing cells in red.A, Anal veins; a-a, anal crossvein; AP, proximal anal cell; AD, distal anal cell; C, costa; Cu, cubitus; M, media; r-m, radial-median crossvein; m-cu, mediocubital crossvein; R, radius; r-rs, radial crossvein; Rs, radial sector; Sc, Subcosta." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3335396/files/figure.png" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">Fig. 28b,e</figureCitation>
); paired high frontal carinae run between the median ocellus and the anterior tentorial pits; circular frontal fovea present; epistomal suture absent; clypeus fused with frons, forming frontoclypeus (
<figureCitation box="[908,1005,1925,1952]" captionStart="FIGURE 28" captionStartId="74.[151,250,1602,1627]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,166,1583]" captionTargetId="figure@74.[151,1436,166,1583]" captionTargetPageId="74" captionText="FIGURE 28. Derecyrta; a-g. Derecyrta risaraldensis sp. nov. ♀ (ICN-MHN ICN_095923); a. Habitus, lateral view, b. Habitus, dorsal view; c. Calcar; d. Head, frontal view; e. Head, lateral view; f. Fore wing; g. pretarsal claws; h. Distal metatarsus; i. D. beechei ♀ (SDEI, photograph by Taeger 2013) habitus, lateral view, j. D. circularis habitus ♀ (NMNH), lateral view. Abbrevia- tion of main veins in blue, cross veins in green, wing cells in red.A, Anal veins; a-a, anal crossvein; AP, proximal anal cell; AD, distal anal cell; C, costa; Cu, cubitus; M, media; r-m, radial-median crossvein; m-cu, mediocubital crossvein; R, radius; r-rs, radial crossvein; Rs, radial sector; Sc, Subcosta." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3335396/files/figure.png" pageId="74" pageNumber="75">Fig. 28d</figureCitation>
); lower margin of frontoclypeus with a short mesial triangular projection; occipital carina present, postgenal carina absent; space between lateral ocelli 0.6 × distance between eye and lateral ocellus, and 0.2 × distance between lateral ocelli and posterior margin of head; malar space long, 2 × diameter of median ocellus; mandibles subquadrate (
<figureCitation box="[975,1071,153,180]" captionStart="FIGURE 28" captionStartId="74.[151,250,1602,1627]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,166,1583]" captionTargetId="figure@74.[151,1436,166,1583]" captionTargetPageId="74" captionText="FIGURE 28. Derecyrta; a-g. Derecyrta risaraldensis sp. nov. ♀ (ICN-MHN ICN_095923); a. Habitus, lateral view, b. Habitus, dorsal view; c. Calcar; d. Head, frontal view; e. Head, lateral view; f. Fore wing; g. pretarsal claws; h. Distal metatarsus; i. D. beechei ♀ (SDEI, photograph by Taeger 2013) habitus, lateral view, j. D. circularis habitus ♀ (NMNH), lateral view. Abbrevia- tion of main veins in blue, cross veins in green, wing cells in red.A, Anal veins; a-a, anal crossvein; AP, proximal anal cell; AD, distal anal cell; C, costa; Cu, cubitus; M, media; r-m, radial-median crossvein; m-cu, mediocubital crossvein; R, radius; r-rs, radial crossvein; Rs, radial sector; Sc, Subcosta." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3335396/files/figure.png" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">Fig. 28d</figureCitation>
), with 3 uniform teeth; maxillary palpus with 6 palpomeres; labial palpus with 4 palpomeres, apical palpomere 2 × length of preapical. Pronotum with short reticulations on lateral ends of transpronotal sulcus. Meso- and metathorax slightly rough, with parallel reticulations on following: posterior area to notauli and anterior to median region of transcutal sulcus, interaxillar sulcus, anterior margin of lateral mesoscutellum, lateral arms of metascutellum, and posterior margin of mesepimeron. Mesoscutellum posterior margin with short mesodorsad spiniform projection (
<figureCitation box="[996,1094,333,359]" captionStart="FIGURE 28" captionStartId="74.[151,250,1602,1627]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,166,1583]" captionTargetId="figure@74.[151,1436,166,1583]" captionTargetPageId="74" captionText="FIGURE 28. Derecyrta; a-g. Derecyrta risaraldensis sp. nov. ♀ (ICN-MHN ICN_095923); a. Habitus, lateral view, b. Habitus, dorsal view; c. Calcar; d. Head, frontal view; e. Head, lateral view; f. Fore wing; g. pretarsal claws; h. Distal metatarsus; i. D. beechei ♀ (SDEI, photograph by Taeger 2013) habitus, lateral view, j. D. circularis habitus ♀ (NMNH), lateral view. Abbrevia- tion of main veins in blue, cross veins in green, wing cells in red.A, Anal veins; a-a, anal crossvein; AP, proximal anal cell; AD, distal anal cell; C, costa; Cu, cubitus; M, media; r-m, radial-median crossvein; m-cu, mediocubital crossvein; R, radius; r-rs, radial crossvein; Rs, radial sector; Sc, Subcosta." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3335396/files/figure.png" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">Fig. 28a</figureCitation>
). Cenchri narrow and semicircular. Mesopleuron with horizontal pleural suture obliterated posteroventrally. Fore wing (
<figureCitation box="[1166,1258,369,396]" captionStart="FIGURE 28" captionStartId="74.[151,250,1602,1627]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,166,1583]" captionTargetId="figure@74.[151,1436,166,1583]" captionTargetPageId="74" captionText="FIGURE 28. Derecyrta; a-g. Derecyrta risaraldensis sp. nov. ♀ (ICN-MHN ICN_095923); a. Habitus, lateral view, b. Habitus, dorsal view; c. Calcar; d. Head, frontal view; e. Head, lateral view; f. Fore wing; g. pretarsal claws; h. Distal metatarsus; i. D. beechei ♀ (SDEI, photograph by Taeger 2013) habitus, lateral view, j. D. circularis habitus ♀ (NMNH), lateral view. Abbrevia- tion of main veins in blue, cross veins in green, wing cells in red.A, Anal veins; a-a, anal crossvein; AP, proximal anal cell; AD, distal anal cell; C, costa; Cu, cubitus; M, media; r-m, radial-median crossvein; m-cu, mediocubital crossvein; R, radius; r-rs, radial crossvein; Rs, radial sector; Sc, Subcosta." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3335396/files/figure.png" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">Fig. 28f</figureCitation>
) with crossvein 2r-rs absent; intercostal crossvein Sc1 distad to Rs; section of vein M from M+Cu1 shorter (0.5 ×) than section of vein Rs section from Sc+R; 1m-cu curved out distally; crossvein 2r-m length 0.5 × of 3r-m length (
<figureCitation box="[1251,1345,441,468]" captionStart="FIGURE 28" captionStartId="74.[151,250,1602,1627]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,166,1583]" captionTargetId="figure@74.[151,1436,166,1583]" captionTargetPageId="74" captionText="FIGURE 28. Derecyrta; a-g. Derecyrta risaraldensis sp. nov. ♀ (ICN-MHN ICN_095923); a. Habitus, lateral view, b. Habitus, dorsal view; c. Calcar; d. Head, frontal view; e. Head, lateral view; f. Fore wing; g. pretarsal claws; h. Distal metatarsus; i. D. beechei ♀ (SDEI, photograph by Taeger 2013) habitus, lateral view, j. D. circularis habitus ♀ (NMNH), lateral view. Abbrevia- tion of main veins in blue, cross veins in green, wing cells in red.A, Anal veins; a-a, anal crossvein; AP, proximal anal cell; AD, distal anal cell; C, costa; Cu, cubitus; M, media; r-m, radial-median crossvein; m-cu, mediocubital crossvein; R, radius; r-rs, radial crossvein; Rs, radial sector; Sc, Subcosta." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3335396/files/figure.png" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">Fig. 28f</figureCitation>
). Calcar of protibiae curved, tapering distally, with two triangular apical teeth and short velum on inner ventral margin (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 28" captionStartId="74.[151,250,1602,1627]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,166,1583]" captionTargetId="figure@74.[151,1436,166,1583]" captionTargetPageId="74" captionText="FIGURE 28. Derecyrta; a-g. Derecyrta risaraldensis sp. nov. ♀ (ICN-MHN ICN_095923); a. Habitus, lateral view, b. Habitus, dorsal view; c. Calcar; d. Head, frontal view; e. Head, lateral view; f. Fore wing; g. pretarsal claws; h. Distal metatarsus; i. D. beechei ♀ (SDEI, photograph by Taeger 2013) habitus, lateral view, j. D. circularis habitus ♀ (NMNH), lateral view. Abbrevia- tion of main veins in blue, cross veins in green, wing cells in red.A, Anal veins; a-a, anal crossvein; AP, proximal anal cell; AD, distal anal cell; C, costa; Cu, cubitus; M, media; r-m, radial-median crossvein; m-cu, mediocubital crossvein; R, radius; r-rs, radial crossvein; Rs, radial sector; Sc, Subcosta." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3335396/files/figure.png" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">Fig. 28c</figureCitation>
). Metafemur 4 × as long as its width. Claws strongly curved apically, with inner tooth shorter than outer (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 28" captionStartId="74.[151,250,1602,1627]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,166,1583]" captionTargetId="figure@74.[151,1436,166,1583]" captionTargetPageId="74" captionText="FIGURE 28. Derecyrta; a-g. Derecyrta risaraldensis sp. nov. ♀ (ICN-MHN ICN_095923); a. Habitus, lateral view, b. Habitus, dorsal view; c. Calcar; d. Head, frontal view; e. Head, lateral view; f. Fore wing; g. pretarsal claws; h. Distal metatarsus; i. D. beechei ♀ (SDEI, photograph by Taeger 2013) habitus, lateral view, j. D. circularis habitus ♀ (NMNH), lateral view. Abbrevia- tion of main veins in blue, cross veins in green, wing cells in red.A, Anal veins; a-a, anal crossvein; AP, proximal anal cell; AD, distal anal cell; C, costa; Cu, cubitus; M, media; r-m, radial-median crossvein; m-cu, mediocubital crossvein; R, radius; r-rs, radial crossvein; Rs, radial sector; Sc, Subcosta." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3335396/files/figure.png" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">
Fig. 
<quantity box="[151,197,549,576]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="kg" metricValue="2.8" pageId="75" pageNumber="76" unit="g" value="28.0">28g</quantity>
,h
</figureCitation>
). Metabasitarsus length 0.4 × of entire metatarsus. Tarsal plantulae lobes absent. Tibial preapical spurs absent. Subquadrate plates of abdominal tergum I (T1) rough with mesial margin smooth; abdominal segments II, VIII and IX twice as long as remaining segments (
<figureCitation box="[612,710,621,648]" captionStart="FIGURE 28" captionStartId="74.[151,250,1602,1627]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,166,1583]" captionTargetId="figure@74.[151,1436,166,1583]" captionTargetPageId="74" captionText="FIGURE 28. Derecyrta; a-g. Derecyrta risaraldensis sp. nov. ♀ (ICN-MHN ICN_095923); a. Habitus, lateral view, b. Habitus, dorsal view; c. Calcar; d. Head, frontal view; e. Head, lateral view; f. Fore wing; g. pretarsal claws; h. Distal metatarsus; i. D. beechei ♀ (SDEI, photograph by Taeger 2013) habitus, lateral view, j. D. circularis habitus ♀ (NMNH), lateral view. Abbrevia- tion of main veins in blue, cross veins in green, wing cells in red.A, Anal veins; a-a, anal crossvein; AP, proximal anal cell; AD, distal anal cell; C, costa; Cu, cubitus; M, media; r-m, radial-median crossvein; m-cu, mediocubital crossvein; R, radius; r-rs, radial crossvein; Rs, radial sector; Sc, Subcosta." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3335396/files/figure.png" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">Fig. 28b</figureCitation>
); urotergum X (T10) subquadrate, much smaller than all anterior abdominal terga. Cerci long, 4 × as long as its width, rounded apically, in dorsal view slightly longer than urotergum X. Third valvulae in lateral view same length as tergum I. Pilosity white, covering frons, malar space, base of mandibles, propleura, pronotum, mesopleura and abdominal tergum IX.
</paragraph>
