) habitus, lateral view, j. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Smith" authorityYear="1988" box="[861,990,1675,1699]" class="Insecta" family="Xiphydriidae" genus="Derecyrta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="74" pageNumber="75" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="circularis">
<emphasis box="[861,990,1675,1699]" italics="true" pageId="74" pageNumber="75">D. circularis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
habitus ♀ (NMNH), lateral view. Abbrevia- tion of main veins in blue, cross veins in green, wing cells in red. A, Anal veins; a-a, anal crossvein; AP, proximal anal cell; AD, distal anal cell; C, costa; Cu, cubitus; M, media; r-m, radial-median crossvein; m-cu, mediocubital crossvein; R, radius; r-rs, radial crossvein; Rs, radial sector; Sc, Subcosta.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="75.[151,1437,153,1547]" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">
<emphasis box="[199,274,765,791]" italics="true" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">Color:</emphasis>
Body mostly black, with many creamy white spots. Head mainly black, with a white trapezoid spot on frontoclypeus, and a couple of wide white bands along dorsomesial margin of eyes, extending to vertex, ventrally covering malar space, expanding posteriorly to temple (
<figureCitation box="[779,898,837,864]" captionStart="FIGURE 28" captionStartId="74.[151,250,1602,1627]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,166,1583]" captionTargetId="figure@74.[151,1436,166,1583]" captionTargetPageId="74" captionText="FIGURE 28. Derecyrta; a-g. Derecyrta risaraldensis sp. nov. ♀ (ICN-MHN ICN_095923); a. Habitus, lateral view, b. Habitus, dorsal view; c. Calcar; d. Head, frontal view; e. Head, lateral view; f. Fore wing; g. pretarsal claws; h. Distal metatarsus; i. D. beechei ♀ (SDEI, photograph by Taeger 2013) habitus, lateral view, j. D. circularis habitus ♀ (NMNH), lateral view. Abbrevia- tion of main veins in blue, cross veins in green, wing cells in red.A, Anal veins; a-a, anal crossvein; AP, proximal anal cell; AD, distal anal cell; C, costa; Cu, cubitus; M, media; r-m, radial-median crossvein; m-cu, mediocubital crossvein; R, radius; r-rs, radial crossvein; Rs, radial sector; Sc, Subcosta." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3335396/files/figure.png" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">Fig. 28d,e</figureCitation>
). Antenna mainly black, with antennomeres 13- 20 white (
<figureCitation box="[268,369,873,900]" captionStart="FIGURE 28" captionStartId="74.[151,250,1602,1627]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,166,1583]" captionTargetId="figure@74.[151,1436,166,1583]" captionTargetPageId="74" captionText="FIGURE 28. Derecyrta; a-g. Derecyrta risaraldensis sp. nov. ♀ (ICN-MHN ICN_095923); a. Habitus, lateral view, b. Habitus, dorsal view; c. Calcar; d. Head, frontal view; e. Head, lateral view; f. Fore wing; g. pretarsal claws; h. Distal metatarsus; i. D. beechei ♀ (SDEI, photograph by Taeger 2013) habitus, lateral view, j. D. circularis habitus ♀ (NMNH), lateral view. Abbrevia- tion of main veins in blue, cross veins in green, wing cells in red.A, Anal veins; a-a, anal crossvein; AP, proximal anal cell; AD, distal anal cell; C, costa; Cu, cubitus; M, media; r-m, radial-median crossvein; m-cu, mediocubital crossvein; R, radius; r-rs, radial crossvein; Rs, radial sector; Sc, Subcosta." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3335396/files/figure.png" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">Fig. 28b</figureCitation>
). Pronotum mainly white, with dorsal and posterior margins of lateral lobes white; propleura black; mesonotum mainly black, with posterior half of median lobe of mesoscutum, dorsal region of axillae and mesoscutellum white; mesoscutellum with small black spot apically; metanotum black with metascutellum white, and pair of white spots posterior to each cenchrus. Mesopleuron black with superior half of episternum white; metapleuron black (
<figureCitation box="[318,434,1017,1044]" captionStart="FIGURE 28" captionStartId="74.[151,250,1602,1627]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,166,1583]" captionTargetId="figure@74.[151,1436,166,1583]" captionTargetPageId="74" captionText="FIGURE 28. Derecyrta; a-g. Derecyrta risaraldensis sp. nov. ♀ (ICN-MHN ICN_095923); a. Habitus, lateral view, b. Habitus, dorsal view; c. Calcar; d. Head, frontal view; e. Head, lateral view; f. Fore wing; g. pretarsal claws; h. Distal metatarsus; i. D. beechei ♀ (SDEI, photograph by Taeger 2013) habitus, lateral view, j. D. circularis habitus ♀ (NMNH), lateral view. Abbrevia- tion of main veins in blue, cross veins in green, wing cells in red.A, Anal veins; a-a, anal crossvein; AP, proximal anal cell; AD, distal anal cell; C, costa; Cu, cubitus; M, media; r-m, radial-median crossvein; m-cu, mediocubital crossvein; R, radius; r-rs, radial crossvein; Rs, radial sector; Sc, Subcosta." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3335396/files/figure.png" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">Fig. 28a,b</figureCitation>
). Legs mostly black, with dorsal region of coxae, ventral region of femora and tibiae white (apex of tibiae black). Wings hyaline with veins brown. Abdomen mainly black, with mesal margin of tergum I and transverse band on the middle of tergum II to VIII white (
<figureCitation box="[804,922,1089,1116]" captionStart="FIGURE 28" captionStartId="74.[151,250,1602,1627]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,166,1583]" captionTargetId="figure@74.[151,1436,166,1583]" captionTargetPageId="74" captionText="FIGURE 28. Derecyrta; a-g. Derecyrta risaraldensis sp. nov. ♀ (ICN-MHN ICN_095923); a. Habitus, lateral view, b. Habitus, dorsal view; c. Calcar; d. Head, frontal view; e. Head, lateral view; f. Fore wing; g. pretarsal claws; h. Distal metatarsus; i. D. beechei ♀ (SDEI, photograph by Taeger 2013) habitus, lateral view, j. D. circularis habitus ♀ (NMNH), lateral view. Abbrevia- tion of main veins in blue, cross veins in green, wing cells in red.A, Anal veins; a-a, anal crossvein; AP, proximal anal cell; AD, distal anal cell; C, costa; Cu, cubitus; M, media; r-m, radial-median crossvein; m-cu, mediocubital crossvein; R, radius; r-rs, radial crossvein; Rs, radial sector; Sc, Subcosta." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3335396/files/figure.png" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">Fig. 28a,b</figureCitation>
); tergum IX mainly black, with pair of lateral large white C-shaped bands surrounding the posteroventral margin; tergum × white. Abdominal sterna dark brown with yellow median spot on each. Cerci black. 2 
<superScript attach="left" box="[691,707,1160,1174]" fontSize="6" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">nd</superScript>
valvifers and 3 
<superScript attach="left" box="[881,894,1160,1174]" fontSize="6" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">th</superScript>
valvulae (ovipositor sheath) black.
</paragraph>
