<paragraph blockId="75.[151,1437,153,1547]" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">
<emphasis box="[199,746,1341,1367]" italics="true" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">
Remarks: 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Malagón-Aldana &amp; Smith &amp; Vilhelmsen &amp; Serna" authorityYear="2019" box="[316,587,1341,1367]" class="Insecta" family="Xiphydriidae" genus="Derecyrta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="75" pageNumber="76" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="risaraldensis">Derecyrta risaraldensis</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Smith" authorityYear="1988" box="[601,746,1341,1367]" class="Insecta" family="Xiphydriidae" genus="Derecyrta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="75" pageNumber="76" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="circularis">D. circularis</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[806,928,1341,1367]" class="Insecta" family="Xiphydriidae" genus="Derecyrta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="75" pageNumber="76" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="beechei">
<emphasis box="[806,928,1341,1367]" italics="true" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">D. beechei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
each have different combinations of yellow spots on a black background. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Smith" authorityYear="1988" box="[480,622,1377,1403]" class="Insecta" family="Xiphydriidae" genus="Derecyrta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="75" pageNumber="76" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="circularis">
<emphasis box="[480,500,1378,1403]" italics="true" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">D</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[514,622,1377,1403]" italics="true" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">circularis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[636,724,1377,1404]" captionStart="FIGURE 28" captionStartId="74.[151,250,1602,1627]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,166,1583]" captionTargetId="figure@74.[151,1436,166,1583]" captionTargetPageId="74" captionText="FIGURE 28. Derecyrta; a-g. Derecyrta risaraldensis sp. nov. ♀ (ICN-MHN ICN_095923); a. Habitus, lateral view, b. Habitus, dorsal view; c. Calcar; d. Head, frontal view; e. Head, lateral view; f. Fore wing; g. pretarsal claws; h. Distal metatarsus; i. D. beechei ♀ (SDEI, photograph by Taeger 2013) habitus, lateral view, j. D. circularis habitus ♀ (NMNH), lateral view. Abbrevia- tion of main veins in blue, cross veins in green, wing cells in red.A, Anal veins; a-a, anal crossvein; AP, proximal anal cell; AD, distal anal cell; C, costa; Cu, cubitus; M, media; r-m, radial-median crossvein; m-cu, mediocubital crossvein; R, radius; r-rs, radial crossvein; Rs, radial sector; Sc, Subcosta." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3335396/files/figure.png" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">Fig. 28j</figureCitation>
) has the entire antenna black, narrow subocular stripe bands not extending dorsally beyond the antenna, thorax mostly black with a small spot in the dorsal corner of mesepisternum, and legs entirely black. In 
<taxonomicName box="[457,579,1449,1475]" class="Insecta" family="Xiphydriidae" genus="Derecyrta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="75" pageNumber="76" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="beechei">
<emphasis box="[457,579,1449,1475]" italics="true" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">D. beechei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[596,687,1449,1476]" captionStart="FIGURE 28" captionStartId="74.[151,250,1602,1627]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,166,1583]" captionTargetId="figure@74.[151,1436,166,1583]" captionTargetPageId="74" captionText="FIGURE 28. Derecyrta; a-g. Derecyrta risaraldensis sp. nov. ♀ (ICN-MHN ICN_095923); a. Habitus, lateral view, b. Habitus, dorsal view; c. Calcar; d. Head, frontal view; e. Head, lateral view; f. Fore wing; g. pretarsal claws; h. Distal metatarsus; i. D. beechei ♀ (SDEI, photograph by Taeger 2013) habitus, lateral view, j. D. circularis habitus ♀ (NMNH), lateral view. Abbrevia- tion of main veins in blue, cross veins in green, wing cells in red.A, Anal veins; a-a, anal crossvein; AP, proximal anal cell; AD, distal anal cell; C, costa; Cu, cubitus; M, media; r-m, radial-median crossvein; m-cu, mediocubital crossvein; R, radius; r-rs, radial crossvein; Rs, radial sector; Sc, Subcosta." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3335396/files/figure.png" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">
Fig. 
<date box="[650,687,1449,1476]" pageId="75" pageNumber="76" value="1928-01">28i</date>
</figureCitation>
) the antenna is brown, with 27 antennomeres; malar space black; thorax black with mesoscutellum yellow. In addition, 
<taxonomicName box="[751,837,1485,1511]" class="Insecta" family="Xiphydriidae" genus="Derecyrta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="75" pageNumber="76" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="beechei">
<emphasis box="[751,837,1485,1511]" italics="true" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">beechei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is exceptional in having the crossvein 2r-rs and tarsal plantulae, which are absent in the remaining species (
<bibRefCitation author="Smith, D. R." box="[749,899,1520,1547]" pageId="75" pageNumber="76" pagination="21 - 24" refId="ref85510" refString="Smith, D. R. (1995 b) A new species of Xiphydriidae (Hymenoptera) from Chile. Revista Chilena de Entomologia, 22, 21 - 24." type="journal article" year="1995">Smith 1995b</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
